rier functions as a formal approach to constraint-based control design, and provides an in-depth look at the design of the SlothBot, a slow and energy-efficient robot used for environmental monitoring and conservation.Visionary in scope, Robot Ecology presents a comprehensive and unified methodology for designing robots that can function over long durations in diverse natural environments.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aAutonomous robotsxDesign and construction. 0aRoboticsxEnvironmental aspects. 0aRobotsxControl systems. 7aTechnology & Engineering / Robotics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073912140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691230078423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691230078/original  a978-3-11-073912-1  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK